<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 1:52AM CDT  by NWS Wichita</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Chautauqua County
through 230 AM CDT...
At 151 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sedan, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sedan, Peru, Chautauqua, Elgin, Niotaze and Hale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
